notesStmt.note: Defective at the beginning and at the end.
Natana᾿el ben Zekhariah Rafa᾿el, Nurstadt, dated [5]436 (1676): folio 1 (inner flyleaf).
Liṿon ben Mosheh and Rafa᾿el ben Me᾿ir Piḳarṭo: inscribed, folio 261r.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A festival prayer book with services for Rosh ha-Shanah, Yom Kipur and Sukot, according to the German rite.

msItem.title: Services for the first day of Rosh ha-Shanah
Services for the second day of Rosh ha-Shanah

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 25; written lines: 24; Uniform layout. Visible pricking and plummet ruling. Initial words written in much larger characters. Hair side and flesh side hardly distinguishable.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi square script, punctuated, of the 14th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Brown leather, blind-tooled. Boxed. Spine: 'Machazor. Juxta Ritum Germanicum. Hebraice. Mus. Brit. Jure Emptionis. 18, 968.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Adolphus Asher (b. 1800, d. 1853), Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153: purchased from him on 12 June 1852: inscribed, folio 261v.
